name: The Crown
overview:
The gripping, decades-spanning inside story of Her Majesty Queen Elizabeth II and the Prime Ministers who shaped Britain's post-war destiny. 

The Crown tells the inside story of two of the most famous addresses in the world – Buckingham Palace and 10 Downing Street – and the intrigues, love lives and machinations behind the great events that shaped the second half of the 20th century. Two houses, two courts, one Crown.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: As a young Elizabeth becomes Queen, she must manage major political issues and personal matters, which often clash in ways she never imagined.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: As a new era begins, Queen Elizabeth struggles to navigate a world that's changing around her while preserving both the monarchy and her marriage.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: As the 1960s and '70s unfold, the royal family contends with conflict and betrayal while striving to uphold tradition in the face of an evolving world.

seasons.name: Season 4
seasons.overview: As the 1970s are drawing to a close, Queen Elizabeth and her family find themselves preoccupied with safeguarding the line of succession by securing an appropriate bride for Prince Charles, who is still unmarried at 30.

seasons.name: Season 5
seasons.overview: Diana and Charles wage a media war. The monarchy's role is up for debate. Welcome to the '90s — and Queen Elizabeth II's biggest challenge to date.

seasons.name: Season 6
seasons.overview: Season 6, Part 1 continues with Princess Diana's and explores the events surrounding her tragic death in 1997. Season 6, Part 2 sees Queen Elizabeth II reflect on her reign and look ahead to a time when her successors will take the throne.

episodes.overview: With King George too ill to travel, Elizabeth and Philip embark on a four-continent Commonwealth tour. Party leaders attempt to undermine Churchill.

episodes.name: Windsor
episodes.overview: With Elizabeth in a new role, Philip tries to assert some power. Churchill wants to delay the coronation. King George’s disgraced brother arrives.

episodes.name: Act of God

episodes.name: Smoke and Mirrors
episodes.overview: Elizabeth rejects protocol by appointing Philip to coordinate her coronation, but his ideas create conflict. The Duke of Windsor returns to London.

guest_stars.name: Rosalind Knight

guest_stars.name: Lia Williams

episodes.name: Gelignite
episodes.overview: Margaret and Peter come to Elizabeth with a request. With a royal scandal about to break in the newspapers, the Queen Mother intervenes.

guest_stars.character: Wallis Simpson / Wallis, Duchess of Windsor
guest_stars.name: Lia Williams

episodes.name: Scientia Potentia Est
episodes.overview: As the Soviets test the H-bomb, both Churchill and Eden have major health crises. Angry about her inadequate education, Elizabeth hires a tutor.

episodes.name: Pride & Joy
episodes.overview: Elizabeth and Philip go on an exhausting world journey. Margaret takes over some of her sister’s official duties and tries to liven things up.

episodes.name: Assassins
episodes.overview: As tensions with Philip increase, Elizabeth spends time with her old friend Porchey. Churchill’s portrait is painted for his 80th birthday.

episodes.name: Gloriana
episodes.overview: Margaret and Peter are reunited, but another obstacle stands in their way. Elizabeth is torn between her duty as Queen and her love for her sister.

1.name: Season 1
1.overview: As a young Elizabeth becomes Queen, she must manage major political issues and personal matters, which often clash in ways she never imagined.

episodes.name: Misadventure
episodes.overview: As Philip leaves for a long tour, Elizabeth makes an upsetting discovery. Prime Minister Eden wants to strike back after Egypt seizes the Suez Canal.

episodes.name: A Company of Men
episodes.overview: Elizabeth feels disconnected from Philip. Eden copes with international pressure and ill health. An interview stirs up harrowing memories for Philip.

episodes.name: Lisbon
episodes.overview: Palace insiders try to prevent a scandal that could reflect poorly on Philip. Eden faces censure from his cabinet and the press.

episodes.name: Beryl
episodes.overview: When Elizabeth and Philip throw a grand party for their 10th anniversary, both Margaret and the new Prime Minister experience romantic tribulations.

guest_stars.character: Wallis Simpson / Wallis, Duchess of Windsor
guest_stars.name: Lia Williams

episodes.name: Marionettes
episodes.overview: After Elizabeth makes a tone-deaf speech at a Jaguar factory, she and the monarchy come under public attack from an outspoken lord.

episodes.name: Vergangenheit
episodes.overview: A secret World War II document opens Elizabeth's eyes to grim realities about a family member. The Duke of Windsor campaigns to re-enter public life.

guest_stars.character: Wallis Simpson / Wallis, Duchess of Windsor
guest_stars.name: Lia Williams

episodes.name: Matrimonium
episodes.overview: A letter from Peter Townsend spurs Margaret to make a bold proposal. Elizabeth has good news that causes complications for Margaret.

episodes.name: Dear Mrs. Kennedy
episodes.overview: Inspired by Jackie Kennedy and against her government's wishes, Elizabeth takes an unconventional approach to resolving an issue with Ghana.

episodes.name: Paterfamilias
episodes.overview: Philip insists that Prince Charles attend his alma mater in Scotland and reminisces about the life-changing difficulties he experienced there.

episodes.name: Mystery Man
episodes.overview: A salacious government scandal hits close to home for Elizabeth and Philip. Elizabeth retreats to Scotland for rest during a difficult pregnancy.

2.name: Season 2
2.overview: As a new era begins, Queen Elizabeth struggles to navigate a world that's changing around her while preserving both the monarchy and her marriage.

episodes.name: Olding
episodes.overview: The royal family mourns the passing of Winston Churchill. The United Kingdom ushers in a new prime minister, the Labour Party's Harold Wilson whom Prince Philip and Queen Elizabeth hear might be a Soviet spy.

episodes.name: Margaretology
episodes.overview: While Princess Margaret and Lord Snowdon visit the USA, the queen, at the bidding of Harold Wilson, asks them to make a side trip to Washington, D.C. to ask President Johnson for financial assistance for the United Kingdom.

episodes.name: Aberfan
episodes.overview: A horrible disaster in the Welsh town of Aberfan leaves scores of children dead, but when the Queen takes a week to decide to visit the town to offer solace to its people, she must confront her reasons for postponing the trip.

episodes.name: Bubbikins
episodes.overview: Left without a home by a political coup in Athens, Philip's eccentric mother, Princess Alice of Greece, is invited to live in Buckingham Palace by the Queen.

episodes.name: Coup
episodes.overview: While the Queen travels abroad to learn about horse training, unhappiness among the British elite with the devaluation of the pound involves Lord Mountbatten in a plan to oust Harold Wilson.

episodes.name: Tywysog Cymru
episodes.overview: Prince Charles is sent to Aberystwyth to learn Welsh from an ardent nationalist in preparation for the ceremony for his investiture as Prince of Wales.

episodes.name: Moondust
episodes.overview: The 1969 moon landing occasions a mid-life crisis in Prince Philip, who thinks of the adventures he has missed as the Queen's consort.

episodes.name: Dangling Man
episodes.overview: Charles visits the exiled Duke of Windsor in his Paris chateau, only to find him very ill. But will the Queen make peace with her uncle before he dies?

episodes.name: Imbroglio
episodes.overview: While Princess Anne dates her elder brother's polo rival Andrew Parker Bowles, Prince Charles falls deeply in love with Camilla Shand causing the Queen Mother and Lord Mountbatten to interfere.

episodes.name: Cri de Coeur
episodes.overview: As her marriage falls apart, Princess Margaret finds solace in the arms of a much younger landscape gardener. The Queen and the nation celebrate Elizabeth II's Silver Jubilee.

3.name: Season 3
3.overview: As the 1960s and '70s unfold, the royal family contends with conflict and betrayal while striving to uphold tradition in the face of an evolving world.

episodes.name: Gold Stick
episodes.overview: As Elizabeth welcomes Britain's first woman prime minister and Charles meets a young Diana Spencer, an IRA attack brings tragedy to the royal family.

episodes.name: The Balmoral Test
episodes.overview: Margaret Thatcher visits Balmoral but has trouble fitting in with the royal family, while Charles finds himself torn between his heart and family duty.

episodes.name: Fairytale
episodes.overview: After Charles proposes, Diana moves into Buckingham Palace and finds her life filled with princess training, loneliness — and Camilla Parker Bowles.

episodes.name: Favourites
episodes.overview: While Margaret Thatcher struggles with the disappearance of her favorite child, Elizabeth reexamines her relationships with her four children.

episodes.name: Fagan
episodes.overview: As Thatcher's policies create rising unemployment, a desperate man breaks into the palace, where he finds Elizabeth's bedroom and awakens her for a talk.

episodes.name: Terra Nullius
episodes.overview: On a tour of Australia, Diana struggles to balance motherhood with her royal duties while both she and Charles cope with their marriage difficulties.

episodes.name: The Hereditary Principle
episodes.overview: Grappling with mental health issues, Margaret seeks help and discovers an appalling secret about estranged relatives of the royal family.
As many nations condemn apartheid in South Africa, tension mounts between Thatcher and Elizabeth over their clashing opinions on applying sanctions.

guest_stars.character: Young Elizabeth / Young Queen Elizabeth II
guest_stars.name: Claire Foy

episodes.name: Avalanche
episodes.overview: Charles is caught in a deadly avalanche, prompting both him and Diana to reevaluate their commitment to their troubled marriage.

episodes.name: War
episodes.overview: Amid a growing challenge to her power, Thatcher fights for her position. Charles grows more determined to separate from Diana as their marriage unravels.

4.name: Season 4
4.overview: As the 1970s are drawing to a close, Queen Elizabeth and her family find themselves preoccupied with safeguarding the line of succession by securing an appropriate bride for Prince Charles, who is still unmarried at 30.

episodes.name: Queen Victoria Syndrome
episodes.overview: A much-needed update to the Royal Yacht draws scrutiny to the Queen's reign. Hounded by the press, Charles and Diana have a second honeymoon in Italy.

guest_stars.character: Young Elizabeth / Young Queen Elizabeth II
guest_stars.name: Claire Foy

episodes.name: The System
episodes.overview: Prince Philip offers his support to a grieving family member. Keen to snatch a scoop, a tabloid journalist approaches Diana about a tell-all book.

episodes.name: Mou Mou
episodes.overview: In 1946, an Egyptian street vendor finds inspiration in the abdicated King Edward. Years later, he eagerly tries to integrate into British High Society.

guest_stars.character: Wallis Simpson / Wallis, Duchess of Windsor
guest_stars.name: Lia Williams

episodes.name: Annus Horribilis
episodes.overview: Between a fire at Windsor Castle and tensions in her children’s marriages, the Queen commemorates and reassesses her 40 years on the throne.

episodes.name: The Way Ahead
episodes.overview: Faced with the fallout of an intercepted call with Camilla and the consequent kickback to his marriage, Prince Charles must navigate a scandal.

episodes.name: Ipatiev House
episodes.overview: Eager to lead a newly democratic Russia, President Yeltsin tries to win the Queen's support while she navigates new rifts in her marriage with Philip.

episodes.name: No Woman's Land
episodes.overview: As BBC's Martin Bashir goes to great lengths to secure an interview with Diana, the lonely princess finds purpose and warmth in a London hospital.

episodes.name: Gunpowder
episodes.overview: The Queen spends quality time with Prince William. On Guy Fawkes Night, fireworks make for a perfect distraction from Diana's BBC interview.

episodes.name: Couple 31
episodes.overview: The Princess of Wales contends with the repercussions of her statements. The Queen asks the Prime Minister for his help in a delicate family matter.

episodes.name: Decommissioned
episodes.overview: After heightened public scrutiny, Charles forges a new alliance in Hong Kong. Mohamed Al-Fayed offers his support to a newly-divorced Diana.

5.name: Season 5
5.overview: Diana and Charles wage a media war. The monarchy's role is up for debate. Welcome to the '90s — and Queen Elizabeth II's biggest challenge to date.

episodes.name: Persona Non Grata
episodes.overview: Diana holidays in Saint-Tropez with Al-Fayed and bonds with his son Dodi. Charles is crushed when the Queen won't attend Camilla's 50th birthday party.

episodes.name: Two Photographs
episodes.overview: Cameras flash and a media circus swirls as Diana and Dodi spend more time together. In retaliation, Charles stages a fatherly photo op with his sons.

episodes.name: Dis-Moi Oui
episodes.overview: Dodi's father urges him to propose, but marriage is the last thing on Diana's mind. Later, a high-speed car chase with paparazzi ends in disaster.

episodes.name: Aftermath
episodes.overview: As the world mourns, the Queen's silence prompts ire and warnings from a grieving Charles. How will she rise to the occasion and mother her nation?

episodes.name: Willsmania
episodes.overview: Hounded by press and adoring girls, 15-year-old William struggles to find stability after Diana's death. Charles enlists his own parents to help his son.

episodes.name: Ruritania
episodes.overview: Eager to improve the monarchy's public image, the Queen seeks out savvy statesman Tony Blair — but the Prime Minister's advice defies royal protocol.

guest_stars.character: Yeoman of the Glass and China
guest_stars.name: Barry McCarthy

episodes.name: Alma Mater
episodes.overview: Now at university, William sets his eyes on Kate Middleton. With meddling parents and other prospects in the mix, how will their connection bloom?

episodes.name: Ritz
episodes.overview: After a series of strokes, a declining Margaret recalls a wild night with her sister at the Ritz in 1945, and later celebrates her 70th birthday there.

episodes.name: Hope Street
episodes.overview: Reeling from loss and wary of her Golden Jubilee, the Queen bonds with William, who finds his footing between normality and life in the royal limelight.

episodes.name: Sleep, Dearie Sleep
episodes.overview: The Queen gives Charles the green light to wed Camilla. Tasked with planning her own funeral ahead of her 80th birthday, she faces an existential crisis.

6.overview: Season 6, Part 1 continues with Princess Diana's and explores the events surrounding her tragic death in 1997. Season 6, Part 2 sees Queen Elizabeth II reflect on her reign and look ahead to a time when her successors will take the throne.
